### 🟠 5. No Rate Limiting

All endpoints are unbounded. An attacker can hammer `/users` or `/health` with thousands of requests per second (enumeration, DoS, credential stuffing on future auth endpoints).

**Fix — Add `express-rate-limit`:**
```bash
