## Executive Summary

The application is a minimal Express server with two endpoints. While the code itself contains no active malicious logic, it is **missing nearly every standard security control** required for production deployment. Seven distinct vulnerabilities are documented below, spanning OWASP A01 (Broken Access Control), A02 (Cryptographic Failures), A05 (Security Misconfiguration), and A09 (Security Logging Failures).

